Headlines.Author: Ned Levin
Headlines.Headline: China Cracks Down on Messaging Apps - Update

PARAGRAPH.#text: China for the first time placed restrictions on instant-messaging services that have become an increasingly popular platform in the country for discussion and debate. Beijing said the restrictions were unveiled to "help build a clean cyberspace" and safeguard national security. The rules apply to users with special accounts that let them post messages broadly on chat apps such as Tencent Holding Ltd.'s WeChat and Alibaba Group Holding Ltd.'s Laiwang. Such so-called public or official accounts let other users subscribe to message feeds, similar to public pages on Facebook.
